-prob_2b.py: Python script problem 2b.


-makefile

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTRUCTIONS:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To compile the code, simply input "make" into the terminal while in the parent
directory. The makefile should point to the correct source code folder.
The makefile should generate an executable "solver" in the parent directory.
Run the executable by typing "./solver" in the command line.

The solver executable will prompt you for a initial guesses for the x and y
values of the roots. Have fun!


To run the python script on oscer, first load in the required module by typing
 "module load /python/anaconda3" in the command line. This is required 
to acces the canned scipy solver. 

Next, run the script by typing "python prob_2b.py" into the terminal.
This script does not include raw input and is only included
for posterity.


